About this item

  • Almighty Audio Custom-designed Nova Acoustic System features best-in class audio for gaming with High Fidelity Drivers. Fully customize your ideal sound experience with a first-in gaming Pro-grade Parametric EQ.
  • 360 degree Spatial Audio - Immersive surround sound transports you to the gaming world, letting you hear every critical step, reload, or vocal cue to give you an advantage. *Fully compatible with Tempest 3D Audio for PS5 / Microsoft Spatial Sound
  • Adjustable for Perfect Fit The ComfortMAX System includes height-adjusting, rotating earcups with AirWeave memory cushion and a stretchy band. The lightweight form of the headset keeps you comfortable no matter how long you play.
  • Bidirectional Noise-Cancelling Mic The ClearCast Gen 2 mic silences background noise by up to 25dB on any platform to give you crystal clear comms. Fully retract the mic into the earcup for a sleeker look.
  • Multi-Platform Support - Easily connect to any gaming console with a 3.5mm jack, such as PlayStation, PC, Xbox, or Switch. Works great with mobile devices as well.
  • Easy Settings On-board controls allow convenient volume adjustment and muting on the headset.

From the manufacturer

Almighty Audio

Steep your ears in incredible Almighty Audio to elevate your gaming experience. Arctis Nova 1P offers the Nova Acoustic System with custom-designed High Fidelity Drivers for stellar audio vibes that will leave you coming back for more.

Nova Acoustic System

360 Spatial Audio

Fully engage with your favorite world as immersive surround sound allows you to identify the direction of every critical step, reload, or vocal cue.

*Fully compatible with Tempest 3D Audio for PS5 / Microsoft Spatial Sound

Pro-grade Parametric EQ

Feel like an audio wizard with Sonar Software and adjust nearly every aspect of sound by using a professional-grade, 10-band Parametric EQ. With a couple of clicks, highlight the head pops and critical enemy footsteps by using presets made with the best esports players.

ComfortMax System

Ultra Lightweight & Slim

Drip check. The Arctis Nova 1P's stylish profile weighs just 236g/0.52lbs, ensuring comfortable wear all day long. Your ears stay cool with AirWeave Memory Foam cushions, keeping you comfy throughout your gaming session.

Height-Adjustable

It's easy to find the perfect fit with 4-points of adjustability. The height-adjustable earcups work for any head size and the flexible, stretchy band distributes the weight evenly.

Noise-Cancelling Microphone

Your keyboard clacks and munching sounds turn lowkey in favor of your voice with the ClearCast Gen 2 mic. The bidirectional broadcast-quality mic lowers distracting sounds by up to 25dB. Retract your mic completely into the earcup for a sleeker look.

Multi-Platform Support

Your Arctis Nova 1P works with many gaming platforms, as the universal 3.5mm jack supports PlayStation, PC, Mac, Xbox, or Switch. Also, vibe on the go with your mobile device.

Onboard Controls

The controls you need are right at your fingertips, as you can easily adjust the volume of the headset and mute yourself when necessary with the touch of a button.

    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2023
    Style: Nova 1PColor: WhiteVerified Purchase
    The Good: This headset has fantastic build quality and I love the colors/material used. The fitment is easy to adjust and it cups my head perfectly, and I don't feel any discomfort after longer periods of use. Its clean, its neat, its comfortable and the audio quality is better than what I would consider average. Its surprisingly hard to find a headset without RGB (that you're not even gonna see anyway cuz its on the sides of your head lol) and this one nailed the overall design. The mic felt flimsy at first but its actually really nice having so much adjustment rather than just a static, swiveling arm like other headsets. It also stores really nicely to keep your space organized.

    The Bad: It took me longer than I'd like to admit to get this thing working.. There were no instructions included, but I found a SteelSeries YouTube tutorial. Turns out I had the cable plugged in backwards and did not know to download their GG app for more settings. The packaging itself feels like I just paid an extra $5 for some stickers I'll never use, and some "ooh's and awe's" effects. Also the cable is a little short which can be an issue on PC if your tower isn't close to you, but it's a toss up because a longer cable would make it a hassle for console/controller users.

    What it would take for me to have given 5 stars?
    Include instructions in the box, or at least a QR code to link your own YouTube unboxing and setup video. Then get rid of the stickers because 99% of them are going to end up in landfills anyway. I don't even care if it drops the price, the stickers just feel like a waste of time/energy/resources.
